==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Involute
<hw>In"vo*lute</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A curve
traced by the end of a string wound upon another curve, or unwound from
it; -- called also <altname>evolvent</altname>. See
<er>Evolute</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Involution</ent>⟦br⟧
